<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2116] Puts and deletes can no longer be applied to the same row with the new client API</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2116</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1304&quot; title=&quot;New client server implementation of how gets and puts are handled. &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1304&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1304&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it seems like one can no longer apply puts and deletes to the same row, and more importantly in the same transaction. Obviously one could use rowLocks but this seems heavy handed for this. Also, it seems that this limitation is solely due to the new API factoring.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
